INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1382,1,'2022-06-23 19:24:29','2022-06-23 19:24:29','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dependency management in JavaScript is the number 1 pain for developers according to the 2021 “<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://2021.stateofjs.com/en-US/opinions\" target=\"_blank\">State of JS</a>” survey. That’s not much of a surprise. Not far behind it in 2nd place, comes code architecture.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/1400/1*vtCMiAn6IFPwZai_5pr0kQ.png\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p id=\"06a0\">When you try to effectively manage dependencies in a monorepo you end up facing these two problems together at the same time. You’re basically up against a&nbsp;<strong>dependency Megazord</strong>. That can be a painful experience.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p id=\"2800\">Monorepos can provide a better developer experience in some cases and advantages in terms of code-sharing in order to, in some cases, make development easier. Many companies from Goole and Uber to startups leverage a monorepo in certain cases to gain these benefits.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p id=\"9b39\">However, choosing a monorepo architecture comes with a price. It leads to many issues, especially at scale, that can make it increasingly hard to develop and maintain the software projects inside it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','How to Easily Manage Dependencies in a JS Monorepo','Dependency management in a JavaScript monorepo is made much simpler with pnpm and Bit. — Dependency management in JavaScript is the number 1 pain for developers according to the 2021 “State of JS” survey','publish','open','open','','how-to-easily-manage-dependencies-in-a-js-monorepo','','','2022-06-23 19:41:09','2022-06-23 19:41:09','',0,'http://softsolutions.local/?p=1382',0,'post','',0);
