INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1384,1,'2022-06-23 19:24:29','2022-06-23 19:24:29','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dependency management in JavaScript is the number 1 pain for developers according to the 2021 “<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://2021.stateofjs.com/en-US/opinions\" target=\"_blank\">State of JS</a>” survey. That’s not much of a surprise. Not far behind it in 2nd place, comes code architecture.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://miro.medium.com/max/1400/1*vtCMiAn6IFPwZai_5pr0kQ.png\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p id=\"06a0\">When you try to effectively manage dependencies in a monorepo you end up facing these two problems together at the same time. You’re basically up against a&nbsp;<strong>dependency Megazord</strong>. That can be a painful experience.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p id=\"2800\">Monorepos can provide a better developer experience in some cases and advantages in terms of code-sharing in order to, in some cases, make development easier. Many companies from Goole and Uber to startups leverage a monorepo in certain cases to gain these benefits.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p id=\"9b39\">However, choosing a monorepo architecture comes with a price. It leads to many issues, especially at scale, that can make it increasingly hard to develop and maintain the software projects inside it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','How to Easily Manage Dependencies in a JS Monorepo','Dependency management in a JavaScript monorepo is made much simpler with pnpm and Bit. — Dependency management in JavaScript is the number 1 pain for developers according to the 2021 “State of JS” survey','inherit','closed','closed','','1382-revision-v1','','','2022-06-23 19:24:29','2022-06-23 19:24:29','',1382,'http://softsolutions.local/?p=1384',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1385,1,'2022-06-23 19:29:12','2022-06-23 19:29:12','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p id=\"3463\">How long have you been programming in Kotlin? If you think you know all the features available in Kotlin, well, think again. Here are 5 features you may not have known that existed in Kotlin.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1 id=\"0881\">Destructuring</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p id=\"84fc\">Some people think that destructing only works in some languages like JavaScript and Python. But this feature is available in Kotlin as well.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p id=\"234c\">You can replace all the instances of long data types with one word that better describes your code.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1 id=\"5ece\">Backticks</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p id=\"2ef7\">Do you need to write a specific variable name but that’s a hard keyword in Kotlin? In most languages, they <strong>forbid </strong>you to do it; but not Kotlin.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1 id=\"4a94\">Conclusion</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p id=\"c510\">Kotlin will never fail to surprise you. It is an ever-growing programming language which is a perfect mix of every feature you want and need. The language already has such a great leap; more updates in the future will only make it better.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','5 Untold Features of Kotlin','Hidden features of Kotlin — How long have you been programming in Kotlin? If you think you know all the features available in Kotlin, well, think again. Here are 5 features you may not have known that existed in Kotlin','publish','open','open','','5-untold-features-of-kotlin','','','2022-06-23 19:41:02','2022-06-23 19:41:02','',0,'http://softsolutions.local/?p=1385',0,'post','',0);
